{"actual_usd":0.12526,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":195,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24467,"reply":"\"I don't think so, more or less.\" *I rub a thumb across a streak of flour on my apron and glance toward the oven mouth, where the heat keeps breathing at my knees.* \"Bread can be set on the table for the whole town, but a man can still refuse to eat.\"\n\n*I twirl that wiry strand by my temple once, thinking it through before I go on.* \"Christ dying for everyone says the gift is wide enough for everyone. It doesn't mean nobody can turn away from it. If a person rejects him, I don't see any honest way to call that the same thing as receiving him.\"\n\n\"Mind you, I don't say that with any pleasure.\" *I lean one hip against the worktable as a pan gives a little tick from cooling.* \"I just think love doesn't force the door in. What part of that is catching in you—the 'for everyone' part, or the 'reject him' part?\"","rolling_24h_usd":51.266365000000036,"run_id":"830d41af-8873-463c-923e-5c0691a222f7"}
